abstract: Brazilian construction giant Odebrecht said Friday that it has “fired” its one-time CEO Marcelo Odebrecht, who this month granted media interviews and reportedly began giving information to the company's compliance department.
snippet: Brazilian construction giant Odebrecht said Friday that it has “fired” its one-time CEO Marcelo Odebrecht, who this month granted media interviews and reportedly began giving information to the company's compliance department.
lead_paragraph: RIO DE JANEIRO — Brazilian construction giant Odebrecht said Friday that it has “fired” its one-time CEO Marcelo Odebrecht, who this month granted media interviews and reportedly began giving information to the company's compliance department.
headline_main: Brazil Building Giant Fires Former CEO Marcelo Odebrecht
headline_print_headline: Brazil Building Giant Fires Former CEO Marcelo Odebrecht

abstract: Venezuelan police detained a lawmaker from Juan Guaido's opposition party on Friday, the party said, the latest in a wave of legal actions against lawmakers ahead of Guaido's bid for re-election as National Assembly leader on Jan. 5.
snippet: Venezuelan police detained a lawmaker from Juan Guaido's opposition party on Friday, the party said, the latest in a wave of legal actions against lawmakers ahead of Guaido's bid for re-election as National Assembly leader on Jan. 5.
lead_paragraph: CARACAS — Venezuelan police detained a lawmaker from Juan Guaido's opposition party on Friday, the party said, the latest in a wave of legal actions against lawmakers ahead of Guaido's bid for re-election as National Assembly leader on Jan. 5.
headline_main: Venezuela Detains Lawmaker Ahead of Guaido Re-election Vote: Opposition
headline_print_headline: Venezuela Detains Lawmaker Ahead of Guaido Re-election Vote: Opposition

abstract: Veteran infielder Ian Kinsler will retire after 14 major league seasons, with one year remaining on his contract, and make a move into the San Diego Padres front office, The Athletic reported Friday.
snippet: Veteran infielder Ian Kinsler will retire after 14 major league seasons, with one year remaining on his contract, and make a move into the San Diego Padres front office, The Athletic reported Friday.
lead_paragraph: Veteran infielder Ian Kinsler will retire after 14 major league seasons, with one year remaining on his contract, and make a move into the San Diego Padres front office, The Athletic reported Friday.
headline_main: Veteran Infielder Kinsler to Retire After 14 Seasons
headline_print_headline: Veteran Infielder Kinsler to Retire After 14 Seasons

abstract: Colombia on Friday ordered Uber to cease its ride-hailing operations in the Andean country, effective immediately, after a judge ruled the company violated competition rules.
snippet: Colombia on Friday ordered Uber to cease its ride-hailing operations in the Andean country, effective immediately, after a judge ruled the company violated competition rules.
lead_paragraph: BOGOTA — Colombia on Friday ordered Uber to cease its ride-hailing operations in the Andean country, effective immediately, after a judge ruled the company violated competition rules.
headline_main: Colombia Orders Uber to Cease Ride-Hailing, Cites Competition Rules Violation
headline_print_headline: Colombia Orders Uber to Cease Ride-Hailing, Cites Competition Rules Violation

abstract: Antitrust officials are supposed to prevent problematic corporate mergers. Instead, they’re helping shepherd deals.
snippet: Antitrust officials are supposed to prevent problematic corporate mergers. Instead, they’re helping shepherd deals.
lead_paragraph: Makan Delrahim, the head of the Justice Department’s antitrust division, is paid by taxpayers to prevent corporate mergers that damage the public interest. Instead of doing this important police work, however, Mr. Delrahim has chosen to cast himself as a deal maker.

abstract: “It’s just not fair,” said the owner of the wine cave, who with his wife has donated millions to Democrats since the 1980s.
snippet: “It’s just not fair,” said the owner of the wine cave, who with his wife has donated millions to Democrats since the 1980s.
lead_paragraph: RUTHERFORD, Calif. — To reach the wine cave that set off a firestorm in this week’s Democratic presidential debate, visitors must navigate a hillside shrouded in mossy oak trees and walk down a brick-and-limestone hallway lined with wine barrels. Inside the room, a strikingly long table made of wood and onyx sits below a raindrop chandelier with 1,500 Swarovski crystals.

abstract: The NBA has sent a proposal to teams calling for a 78-game regular season, along with an in-season tournament for all teams and a reseeding of the playoffs when the field is cut to the final four clubs.

lead_paragraph: MIAMI — The NBA has sent a proposal to teams calling for a 78-game regular season, along with an in-season tournament for all teams and a reseeding of the playoffs when the field is cut to the final four clubs.

abstract: The Senate majority leader has earned the nickname the grim reaper for his iron-fisted grip on the chamber, but an impeachment trial is harder to control.
snippet: The Senate majority leader has earned the nickname the grim reaper for his iron-fisted grip on the chamber, but an impeachment trial is harder to control.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Shattering convention, he held open a Supreme Court seat for 11 months. He twice changed Senate rules to create a record-setting assembly line of conservative federal judicial confirmations. He has been ruthless in his control of the Senate floor, denying Republicans and Democrats alike much opportunity to debate legislation.
